-- South Korean Equity Movers: Posco Declines, SK Hynix Gains
-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 2012-04-26T00:47:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/south-korean-equity-movers-posco-declines-sk-hynix-gains.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  South Korea trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:27 a.m. in Seoul.  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  rose 0.7 percent to 1,975.85, halting a
five-day, 2.1 percent retreat.  Posco (005490 KS), South Korea’s biggest steelmaker,
retreated 0.9 percent to 381,000 won.  Nippon Steel Corp. (5401) ,
Japan’s largest steelmaker, said it sued Posco in Tokyo’s
District Court seeking 100 billion yen (1.2 billion) in damages
from the South Korean company for allegedly using trade secrets
acquired illegally by a former employee.  SK Hynix Inc. (000660)  (000660 KS), the world’s second-largest maker
of computer-memory chips that today reported its third quarterly
loss, climbed 1.1 percent to 27,350 won. Hynix said it expects
prices of dynamic random access memory chips to recover in the
second quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in  Seoul  at 
